details.KeyFacts: MidFirst Bank maintained accounts for and processed 34 payments on behalf of two individuals added to OFAC’s SDN List for 14 days post-designation.  The violations stemmed from MidFirst Bank’s misunderstanding of the frequency of its vendor’s screening of new names added to the SDN List against its existing customer base.
